\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sl260\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 HOLDINGS: [1]-Where employees' religious practice of weekly observing the Sabbath by refraining from work from sundown Friday through sunset Saturday conflicted with their employer's requirement that its production employees work every other Saturday, disputed issues of material fact remained, requiring resolution by the trier of fact, in the employees' Title VII suit; [2]-Title VII required the employer reasonably to accommodate the employees' religious practice, if the employer could do so without incurring undue hardship to its business, but whether the employer had reasonably accommodated the employees' Sabbath observance by a combination of allowing them to use their vacation and other paid time off, as well as permitting them to swap shifts with other employees, and, if not, whether the employer could do so without undue hardship, required resolution by the trier of fact.}
\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs28\b1\i0\cf1 Outcome}
\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sl260\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 Decision reversed; case remanded.}
